definition.value: A glycosylglucose consisting of beta-L-fucopyranose and alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
An L-gulofuranose that has alpha configuration at the anomeric cenrtre.
A glycosylxylose consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose and beta-D-xylofuranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->5) glycosidic bond.
A glycosyl alditol derivative that is 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactitol in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted to the corresponding D-galactopyranosyl derivative.
An alpha-D-Galf-(1->2)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
